**OWASP: A05:2021 – Security Misconfiguration**

Without a centralized error handler, uncaught errors in route handlers will cause Express to return a full stack trace to the client — leaking internal file paths, dependency versions, and application structure.

**Fix:** Add a 4-argument error handler as the very last middleware:

```js
// Must come AFTER all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log internally (use a real logger like pino/winston in production)
  console.error(err.stack);

  // Return a sanitized response — never expose err.message or stack to the client
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: 'An unexpected error occurred.',
